description: From Middle English unlykely, unlikly, unlykly, unlicli, equivalent to un- +â€Ž likely.

adjectives.description: unlikely (comparative unlikelier or more unlikely, superlative unlikeliest or most unlikely)

entries.meaning: Not likely; improbable; not to be reasonably expected.
examples: It's very unlikely that you'll be able to walk perfectly after being in a cast for six months.
In the highly unlikely event of landing in water, lifejackets are stored under the seat.

entries.meaning: Not holding out a prospect of success; likely to fail; unpromising.

adverbs.description: unlikely (comparative more unlikely, superlative most unlikely)

examples: The molecular ion candidates are divided by the testing phase into three categories: rejects, unlikelies, and probables. Differences between each candidate and the prominent peaks in the spectrum are computed.
